description: From Middle English outholden, equivalent to out- +‎ hold. Cognate with Scots outhald (“to outhold”).

verbs.description: outhold (third-person singular simple present outholds, present participle outholding, simple past outheld, past participle outheld or (obsolete) outholden)

entries.meaning: (UK dialectal) To hold out, endure; resist, withstand; keep out by force, exclude.
To hold better than someone or something else.
examples: This new tack outholds the older one.

entries.meaning: (poker) To hold longer than another player.
